		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">curses (programming library)</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<p><b>curses</b> is a <a href="/wiki/Computer_display" title="Computer display" class="mw-redirect">terminal</a> control <a href="/wiki/Library_(computer_science)" title="Library (computer science)" class="mw-redirect">library</a> for <a href="/wiki/Unix-like" title="Unix-like">Unix-like</a> systems, enabling the construction of <a href="/wiki/Text_user_interface" title="Text user interface">text user interface (TUI)</a> applications.</p>
<p>curses is a <a href="http://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/pun" class="extiw" title="wikt:pun">pun</a> on the term "<a href="/wiki/Cursor" title="Cursor">cursor</a> optimization". It is a library of functions that manage an application's display on character-cell terminals (e.g., <a href="/wiki/VT100" title="VT100">VT100</a>).<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
